<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1956-05-30T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1956-05-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="628" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d628">
                        <head>628. Telegram 2068 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d628fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/5–2956. Secret;
                                Priority; Limit Distribution. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1956-05-30">May 30, 1956, 3:50
                                    p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d628-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d628-1"/>
                        <p>2068. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Your 1949. Department believes transmittal text May 25 news conference
                            unnecessary. In light Deptels 2066 and 2067 you will understand why
                            Department prefers you endeavor avoid comment on Chinese prisoner
                            matter.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_HH_1"><hi rend="strong">Hoover</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>